data.comment: The whistle has gone to start the match.
Goal! Danilo gives Enschede a 0-1 lead.
In the minute 2, Great play from Vaclav Cerny to set up the goal.
The home team has substituted Dries Saddiki with John Yeboah. Adrie Koster is thus making his first change.
In the minute 45, Dennis Higler blows to end the first-half.
Sebastian Holmen (Willem II) gets a yellow card.
The second-half is underway at Willem II Stadion.
The home team have replaced Leeroy Owusu with Vincent Schippers. This is the second substitution made today by Adrie Koster.
In the minute 48, Jayden Oosterwolde puts the ball in the net and the away team extend their lead. The score-line now reads 0-2.
Danilo with an assist there.
An attacking Enschede player has been brought down in the area ... It's a penalty!
In the minute 62, Goal! Enschede extend their lead to 0-3 through Danilo.
Gorkem Saglam (Willem II) has received a yellow card from Dennis Higler.
Enschede make their first substitution with Lazaros Lamprou replacing Queensy Menig.
In the minute 66, Jan-Arie Van der Heijden is replacing Gorkem Saglam for Willem II at Willem II Stadion.
Miquel Nelom is booked for the home team.
The home team replace Ole Romeny with Paul Gladon.
In the minute 83, Lazaros Lamprou (Enschede) has received a first yellow card.
Halil Dervisoglu is on a sub for Jesse Bosch for Enschede.
Ron Jans (Enschede) is making a third substitution, with Alexander Jeremejeff replacing Danilo.
In the minute 89, Ramiz Zerrouki is replacing Godfried Roemeratoe for the away team.
Lindon Selahi is on a sub for Vaclav Cerny for Enschede.
It's 0-3 as the referee blows for full-time.
